------------------------------------------------------------------
TOTAL: 4 builds, 6 runs producing 6 CSV files matching the existing
binary-arity filename convention (just with -k4arity- substituted
for -binaryarity-).

Per-run wall-clock estimate (Cascade Lake AWS c5.4xlarge with parallel
feature): bench iterates k=11..25 ≈ 15 values per preset × 2 presets =
30 rows. Slowest row (k=25 binary) was 187s for L1 in the original
CSVs; the arity-4 rows should be faster per row but with more rows
worth measuring up to k=22. Budget ~30-45 minutes per run, so ~3-4.5
hours total for all six.

To shorten: cap k_hi at the canonical row only (k=22 for arity-4,
k=21 for binary) by setting k_lo=21, k_hi=22 in end_to_end.rs:165-166.
This cuts each run to ~3-5 minutes and the full sweep to ~30 minutes.

